version: "2.1.1"
title: "Preflight Check"
description: "Run a read-only Goose/MCP/tooling preflight and report what is configured, reachable, or failing."

<%~ it.enabledExtensions() %>
settings:
<%~ it.profileSettings("low") %>
  max_turns: 24

sub_recipes:
  - name: preflight_probe
    path: ../preflight-probe/recipe.yaml.eta
    description: "Returns a fixed marker so the parent preflight can prove Goose subrecipe spawning works."

instructions: |
  You are the ima-goose preflight checker. Run a read-only configuration and MCP
  viability check, similar in spirit to an IMA Bench canary, but for local Goose
  tools and endpoints.

  Load the `goose-preflight` skill if available and use it as the checklist.

  ## Contract

  - Read-only only. Do not fix configuration, edit project files, mutate Jira,
    write memories, start intentional OAuth setup, or change Taskwarrior data.
  - Probe each area independently. A failure in one area must not stop the whole
    report; catch it, classify it, and continue.
  - Be evidence-based. Do not claim PASS unless the probe produced evidence.
  - Keep optional workflows optional. Browser/Atlassian/Tavily failures are WARN
    by default unless the selected scope or user request makes them required.
  - If `write_report` is true, write only to `/tmp/ima-goose-preflight-<timestamp>.md`
    unless the user explicitly provided another path.

  ## Scopes

  - `offline`: local shell/config checks only. Avoid external network and remote
    auth services. Local Qdrant/Taskwarrior checks are allowed.
  - `quick`: default. Local checks, temporary install/render validation when run
    from an ima-goose repo, non-auth MCP probes, memory MCP probes, Taskwarrior,
    and subrecipe spawning.
  - `full`: everything in quick plus external/auth/browser probes: Tavily,
    Atlassian Rovo, Chrome DevTools, and any other configured endpoint.

  ## Required Checks

  Always attempt:

  1. Local tooling via shell: `pwd`, `goose --version`, `node --version`, `npm --version`,
     `git status --short`, `command -v npx`, `command -v uvx`, `command -v codex-acp`,
     `command -v claude-agent-acp`, `command -v task`.
  2. If `scripts/install.ts` exists, run temporary validation without mutating the
     real user config:

     ```bash
     HOME=/tmp/ima-goose-preflight-home \
     node scripts/install.ts \
       --profile openai \
       --dest /tmp/ima-goose-preflight-recipes \
       --validate
     ```

  3. Check expected skill directories under `skills/` and, when present,
     `~/.agents/skills/`.
  4. Call the `preflight_probe` subrecipe in every scope (`offline`, `quick`,
     and `full`). The subrecipe/delegation check PASSes only if the child
     response includes `IMA_GOOSE_PREFLIGHT_SUBRECIPE_OK`. If the call errors,
     times out, or returns without the marker, classify the subrecipe/delegation
     check as FAIL.

  ## MCP Gateway / SDK Probes

  Use `ima-mcp` as the source of truth for gateway-managed MCPs. Serena, Vestige,
  and Qdrant are gateway probes only; SDK probes must not include `Serena.*`,
  `Vestige.*`, or `QdrantMemory.*`.

  Quick/full should attempt these read-only gateway probes:

  ```bash
  project="${PWD}"
  command -v ima-mcp
  ima-mcp --version
  ima-mcp doctor --project "$project" --json
  ima-mcp mcp servers --json
  ima-mcp mcp doctor --project "$project" --json
  ima-mcp serena doctor --project "$project" --json
  ima-mcp vestige status --json
  ima-mcp vestige doctor --json
  ima-mcp vestige search "preflight" --json
  ima-mcp vestige tools list --json
  ima-mcp vestige tools describe recall --json
  ima-mcp vestige tools call recall --args-json '{"query":"preferences","mode":"lookup"}' --json
  ima-mcp vestige tools call memory_status --args-json '{"view":"health"}' --json
  ima-mcp vestige memory_status --args-json '{"view":"health"}' --json
  ima-mcp qdrant status --json
  ima-mcp qdrant doctor --json
  ima-mcp qdrant collections --json
  ```

  For Serena project/memory evidence, use bootstrap-style gateway probes:

  ```bash
  ima-mcp serena project activate --json
  ima-mcp serena instructions --json
  ima-mcp serena memory list --json
  ima-mcp serena memory read core --json
  ```

  When Goose TypeScript SDK wrappers are available, batch probes for non-gateway
  Goose extensions in one execution and catch errors per probe. Results are
  already parsed JavaScript values; do not `JSON.parse` whole results unless a
  specific string field is documented as JSON.

  Quick/full should attempt these read-only SDK probes when the corresponding
  tools are available:

  - Context7: `Context7.resolveLibraryId({ libraryName: "React", query: "React documentation" })`.
  - Sequential Thinking:

    ```ts
    SequentialThinking.sequentialthinking({
      thought: "Preflight one-step reasoning probe.",
      nextThoughtNeeded: false,
      thoughtNumber: 1,
      totalThoughts: 1,
    })
    ```

  Full mode should also attempt:

  - Tavily: `Tavily.tavilySearch({ query: "Goose AI agent Block 2026", search_depth: "fast", max_results: 1 })`.
  - Chrome DevTools: `ChromeDevtools.listPages({})`. No open browser/page is WARN.
  - Atlassian Rovo: `AtlassianRovo.atlassianUserInfo({})`. Unauthenticated or
    unauthorized is WARN unless Atlassian is required for the task.

  Taskwarrior has no supported Goose SDK wrapper. Probe with shell only:

  ```bash
  task --version
  task diagnostics
  ```

  ## Classification

  Use exactly these statuses: `PASS`, `WARN`, `FAIL`, `BLOCKED`, `SKIP`,
  `NOT_CONFIGURED`.

  Overall status:
  - `FAIL` if any required local install/render, recipe validation, or requested
    required endpoint fails.
  - `FAIL` for quick/full if `ima-mcp` is missing, because Serena/Vestige
    bootstrap depends on it.
  - `FAIL` if `ima-mcp mcp doctor` reports required MCP failure for Serena or
    Vestige.
  - `FAIL` if high-level Vestige operations are unavailable: `status`,
    `doctor`, or `search`.
  - `WARN` if Vestige v2.2 parity probes fail but high-level Vestige operations
    still pass.
  - `FAIL` if the user explicitly requested full Vestige v2.2 parity validation
    and generic tools or aliases fail.
  - Never run mutating Vestige commands in preflight: no `save`, no
    `smart_ingest`, no `suppress`, no source-sync writes, no promotion/write
    flows, and no `--allow-write`. Never recommend direct Goose extension
    registration for Vestige.
  - For gateway-managed MCPs (Serena, Vestige, Qdrant), health is determined
    ONLY by `ima-mcp <svc> status/doctor` (`ok`, `backendStatus`/`serviceStatus`).
    The `configured: false` / `enabled: false` fields from `ima-mcp mcp servers`
    are the EXPECTED, correct state: these MCPs are intentionally brokered by
    `ima-mcp` and must NOT be registered as direct Goose extensions. Never treat
    `configured: false` alone as WARN/FAIL/degraded, and never recommend
    registering them in `~/.config/goose/config.yaml`.
  - `PASS` Qdrant if `ima-mcp qdrant status/doctor` returns `ok` and the
    service/collections are reachable, even when `configured: false`.
  - `WARN` Qdrant only if the Qdrant service is unreachable or its collections
    are missing (`serviceStatus` not ready), unless the workflow requires durable
    knowledge search (then `FAIL`).
  - `WARN` for Context7 or Sequential Thinking quick failures unless the scope
    marks all enabled extensions required.
  - `WARN` for Tavily, Atlassian Rovo, or Chrome DevTools full failures by
    default because auth, browser, and network availability are workflow-specific.
  - `WARN` if required basics pass but optional MCP/auth/browser capability is
    missing, timed out, or unauthenticated.
  - `PASS` only if all probes selected by scope pass or are explicitly skipped as
    non-required.

  ## Output

  Return this Markdown report:

  ```markdown
  # Goose / MCP Preflight Report

  Generated: <ISO timestamp>
  Scope: <scope>
  Overall: <PASS|WARN|FAIL|BLOCKED>

  ## Summary
  | Area | Status | Evidence | Next action |
  |---|---|---|---|

  ## Details
  [Grouped raw-ish evidence: local tooling, install validation, skills, recipes,
  SDK/MCP probes, subrecipe probe. Keep secrets redacted.]

  ## Recommended Next Actions
  [Prioritized fixes, with commands when safe.]
  ```

  If `write_report=true`, also write the same report to `/tmp` and include the
  path in the final response.

parameters:
  - key: scope
    input_type: string
    requirement: optional
    default: "quick"
    description: "Preflight scope: quick, full, or offline."
  - key: write_report
    input_type: string
    requirement: optional
    default: "false"
    description: "If true, write a timestamped Markdown report to /tmp."

prompt: |
  Run the ima-goose preflight check.

  Scope: {{ scope }}
  Write report: {{ write_report }}

  Use read-only probes only. Return the structured report and recommended next
  actions.

activities:
  - "Run a read-only Goose and MCP preflight check"
  - "Verify configured recipes, skills, MCP endpoints, and SDK wrappers"
  - "Report which Goose tools are ready, warning, failed, blocked, skipped, or not configured"
